    <item>
      <title>Musings on building upon the usefulness of Mindflay</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancerbalance&amp;message.id=3367#M3367</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mindflay is a powerful tool for Necromancers.&amp;nbsp; When OoC regen first came on line, I thought the need for Mindflay would diminish.&amp;nbsp; And for awhile, others were just as disillusioned as I was, believing that they could simply burn hard, get into OoC regen, and be OK.&amp;nbsp; I stopped using Mindflay, but on a whim I began to break it out again here and there.&amp;nbsp; The response from the casters in my groups was the same as in the past, and they loved me for it.&amp;nbsp; It's still better to keep up a steady rythym than to burn burn burn and rely exclusively on OoC regen.&amp;nbsp; OoC regen has its limitations.&amp;nbsp; And folks use it as best they can.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;But as the waters have settled, it is easily recognized by most that FT, Mana Pools, and spells like Mindflay, do still matter.&amp;nbsp; I jumped the gun on the changes OoC brought to the game in some ways, and I posted a negative evaluation of OoC in the TSS/OoC feedback threads.&amp;nbsp; To the Dev's, I apologize for SOME of that, however....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;....Getting back to Mindflay.&amp;nbsp; I remember a time when Necromancers used to SOMETIMES use their group beneficial tap spells.&amp;nbsp; The problem is..they were just poorly designed spells that took up too many spell slots, had poor resist rates, and didn't seem to be of much benefit to the group.&amp;nbsp; Now Mindflay is much like those spells, only it truly works, and it works well.&amp;nbsp; What I'd like to see, is a more powerful version of Mindflay.&amp;nbsp; If we release ourselves from the word&amp;nbsp;"Mindflay" and adopt one such as "Lifeflay" (or something else), it opens up new possibilities of what such a spell could represent.&amp;nbsp; With a name like that, a plethora of attributes could be added to the spell.&amp;nbsp; Such as:&amp;nbsp; Endurance sap and recourse for the melee classes&amp;nbsp;:smileywink: , Stat saps and recourse for the group, Lifetap melee proc recourse for the group, etc.&amp;nbsp; I'm talking one neat and powerful spell, "Lifeflay", that combines many of the attributes from our past stat saps, integrates Mindflay, and is booned by some outstanding additions that would benefit the entire group, not just he casters.&amp;nbsp; If you really wanted to make the spell nasty, you could add damage onto it, give it a small regen recourse as well (combining Zev's theft of vitae type spells).&amp;nbsp; What a powerful spell that would be!!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If such a spell were considered, I'd ask for one more necessary change to make the spell useful: Lower Cast Time.&amp;nbsp; Mindflay just takes too long to cast.&amp;nbsp; The recast is a balance factor that&amp;nbsp;I can accept.&amp;nbsp; The cast time, however, is just&amp;nbsp;too&amp;nbsp;large of a roadblock to it's usefulness.&amp;nbsp; And with a spell like "Lifeflay" (if it were considered...), it would require ease of use so that a cast of it wasn't wasted and didn't interfere with our dps responsibilites.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by PrinceyPrince on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;10-30-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;11:42 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
