      <title>why waste the time?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancerbalance&amp;message.id=3347#M3347</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why do we continue to pretend that dev's and what not are listening to our "weekly Q and A" and&amp;nbsp;our "top ten lists" etc... &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I see what's been done with the new expansion (and yeah, i understand some content will most likely change this weekend before it goes live) and i ask what has the last year or so accomplished? I'm not faulting the class reps, i'm faulting the system that implements them and doesn't listen to them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've seen some good ideas recently (not counting the "we want 20% more crits and double crit dmg and immunity to everything" posts) such as abilities to be dragged while FD (which has been a request for a long time, along with group FD spell). i've seen requests for either better mana feed spells or eliminate them completely (the argument being the best one, sed sub, was given to us in luclin, when mana pools were 5k tops at the time... and now they're 12 to 15k and we use same spell?) Someone pointed out years ago, that necros were the **SMURF** children of the eye candy gods... WTD, army of the dead, swarm of decay... none of which really accomplished anything, just something to say "ooh cool". Well, the toy has lost its thrill... &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We've asked for better disease based lines, a cold based line of spells, self only cures/ports, etc... and gotten nothing... we've had kick taken away from our specter, we cant pet pull now, circlet of shadows got nerfed (yeah, long ago, but the day after i sold one for 3k, thinking i could get a new one), robes get clicky times changed 2 years after they come out... and its not just us, its all the classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;the question is, when is enough enough? when are you going to stop nickle and diming not just us, but the entire EQ community? your player base has made mass exoduses for other games... does World of Warcraft ring a bell? they're what, the number one mmorpg&amp;nbsp;2 years in a row now? thats where you super-guilds like afterlife and fires of heaven went. on my server (quellious) two of the longest standing top guilds on the server have disbanded now (vis maior and lotus cult) and it seems alliances are the hot ticket now, if you want to survive, for most guilds... when EQ came out, the joke was "the vision (tm)" because it didnt matter what the community wanted, you were the only game in town and we basically had to pay for the privalige of playing in your fantasy world. thats not the case now. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;i dread bidding on items that drop on raids, or worse, paying good pp for a droppable or attunable item in bazaar, wondering if its going to be nerfed, or made no drop (ie, whatever that cloak was with like 25cha, that got made attunable but the stats got level resticted so you no longer got full stats). when is something thats been in the game 5 years not going to be called a bug and get changed... if someone working for you is that slack, get them the hell out of your company, because they are whats costing you more and more memberships each month. fix it before you implement or SHORTLY thereafter.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;and for the love of innoruuk, LISTEN to what the community wants and quit playing god... implement the desires of the paying customer with expansions rather than some pretty new zones and some new focus and spells that, quite honestly, leave us scratching our heads and saying **SMURF**?&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
