      <title>Class Issue List dead?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancerbalance&amp;message.id=3167#M3167</link>
      <description>So, is this about how it works now?&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
1) The class top 10 issue list is dead (not like it's seen all that much action in months anywyas).&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
2) The class rep (correspondent if you will) gets questions from the class.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
3) The class rep gives 2 questions weekly to Kyth.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
4) Kyth forwards the questions to devs.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
5) Devs may or may not reply to Kyth.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
6) Kyth forwards replies, when they exist, to class reps.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
7) Class reps inform the masses that:&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp; a) Things are working as intended.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp; b) Not at this time.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp; c) Do not have a timeframe.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp; d) [insert sarcastic response here :)]&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
That seems to be something of a convoluted game of telephone, but hey&#xD;
if it works that's all I really care about.&amp;nbsp; Speaking of working,&#xD;
I have yet to see any questions answered for our class.&amp;nbsp; That&#xD;
means our rep isn't asking, Kyth isn't forwarding, dev's aren't&#xD;
replying, Kyth isn't forwarding replies, our class rep isn't replying&#xD;
to us, of I have just missed them and if so mea culpa.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I've heard that many class' top 10 list were peppered with 'gimmee' items that were not going to be considered.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
It makes one wonder which of our items were not up for consideration, and even better why not.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Having that answered may have gone a long way to getting a more&#xD;
reasonable (from the dev's perspective) top 10 list, and may have&#xD;
allowed the list to remain more of a functional working animal for&#xD;
positive in game change.&amp;nbsp; What's done is done though, so now&#xD;
knowing will only help us articulate weekly questions that have a&#xD;
chance of being replied to.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
By the way, what questions have been submitted each week for our class?&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
The mage class board indicated that not all reps have submitted questions (May 12th), hope that wasn't us:&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
http://eq1.eqsummoners.com/viewtopic.php?t=26026&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
